
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class GasStation {
  +id: String
  +address: String
  -fuelPumps: List<FuelPump>
}

class FuelPump {
  +number: int
  +isSelfService: boolean
  -fuels: List<Fuel>
}

class Fuel {
  +name: String
  +octaneRating: double
}

class DailyFuelPrice {
  +date: Date
  +fuel: Fuel
  +gasStation: GasStation
  +pricePerLiter: double
}

class FuelPurchase {
  +id: String
  +fuelPump: FuelPump
  +fuel: Fuel
  +dailyFuelPrice: DailyFuelPrice
  +litersDispensed: double
}

' Associations
GasStation "1" -- "0..*" FuelPump : has
FuelPump "1" -- "0..*" Fuel : offers
GasStation "1" -- "0..*" DailyFuelPrice : archives
Fuel "1" -- "0..*" DailyFuelPrice : applies to
FuelPump "1" -- "0..*" FuelPurchase : used for
DailyFuelPrice "1" -- "0..*" FuelPurchase : associated with

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- A **GasStation** has **FuelPumps**.
- Each **FuelPump** offers a list of **Fuels**.
- A **GasStation** archives **DailyFuelPrices**, which are tied to specific **Fuels**.
- A **FuelPurchase** is made at a **FuelPump**, using a specific **Fuel** and a **DailyFuelPrice**.

